---
description: Use Portolan before making codebase map or architecture claims.
globs:
  - "**/*"
alwaysApply: false
---

When the user asks to map, audit, inspect, understand, or explain this
codebase, first read `agent/START_HERE.md` and follow that portable workflow.

Run Portolan before broad manual architecture claims. Use
`portolan map --root <target-root> --out <run-dir>`, or run
`go run ./cmd/portolan map --root <target-root> --out <run-dir>` from a
Portolan source checkout when no binary is installed. Read `run.json`,
`graph.json`, `findings.jsonl`, and `map.md` before reporting.

Answer from exact local evidence and gap ledger entries. Preserve `unknown`,
`cannot_verify`, and `not_assessed` instead of guessing. Do not fetch network
resources, mutate the repository, or collect credentials unless the user
explicitly approves that boundary. Build, packaging, configuration, release,
smoke-test, and integration repositories are valid targets; do not clone or
fetch referenced component source repositories unless the user explicitly
approves that boundary.
